==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnoliidae
<hw>Magnoliidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a group of families of trees and
shrubs and herbs having well-developed perianths and apocarpous ovaries
and generally regarded as the most primitive extant flowering plants;
contains 36 families including <fam>Magnoliaceae</fam> and
<fam>Ranunculaceae</fam>; sometimes classified as a
superorder.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> subclass Magnoliidae, ranalian complex.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnoliophyta</ent>⟦br⟧
